public class BulkInvoiceItem
extends com.guidewire.pl.persistence.code.BeanBase
implements Retireable, BulkInvoiceItemMethods
    BulkInvoiceItem Describes one item of the BulkInvoice, and corresponds to one line item of the original invoice. It contains data fields that define the reserve line to which the item is to be coded, as well as the amount and the PaymentType.

      • isEditable

        public boolean isEditable()
        Tests whether this BulkInvoiceItem is editable. It is editable if:

        • The status is one of:
          1. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_DRAFT
          2. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_NOTVALID
        or
        • The status of the owning Bulk Invoice is BulkInvoiceStatus.TC_AWAITINGSUBMISSION and the status of this item is one of:
          1. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_APPROVED
          2. BulkInvoiceItemStatus.TC_REJECTED
          3. BulkInvoiceItemStatus#TC_INREVIEW

        Returns:
        true if this BulkInvoiceItem is editable, else false

        public void touch()
        Set's the version of the bean to the next value (i.e. the bean version original value+1) Multiple calls to this method on the same bean will result in the same value being used for the version (i.e. it is idempotent). Calling this method will force the bean to be written to the database and participate fully in the commit cycle e.g. pre-update rules will be run, etc.

      • validateForSubmission

        public boolean validateForSubmission()
        Do any validation required on this invoice item to determine whether check creation should proceed. If validation fails, the item's Explanation should be populated with a description of what failed. Optionally, any fixable problems can be corrected here. Other than setting the Explanation field if validation fails, or fixing problems, changes to the invoice item or any other entity should be avoided.
        Specified by:
        validateForSubmission in interface BulkInvoiceItemMethods
        Returns:
        true if the invoice item passed validation, false otherwise
